Conclusion

lattice package is a fastest when it comes to plotting unless there is a large dataset involved where it is the slowest package. ggplot2 excels at plotting large datasets where it is way more faster than the other two. graphics package generally is the slowest one overall.

If I were to choose a package for plotting it would come down to choice between lattice and ggplot2. However I would pick ggplot2 over lattice due to more intuitive interface (simple things with lattice get tedious at times) and the speed of plotting being comparable (or faster with huge datasets).
